<TEXT>
<P>
 FAST ONE by Paul Cain (Vintage: $9; 171 pp., paperback original). Long out of 
print, "Fast One" is the only novel by George Carroll Syms, an enigmatic 
author/screen writer who worked under a variety of pseudonyms. He takes the 
reader on a journey down the mean streets of Depression-era Los Angeles as he 
recounts the rise and fall of the amoral, murderous Gerard Kells, a small-time 
operator so crooked he'd double cross an intersection if he got the chance. 
Kells tries to oust the biggest racketeers in the city, but his eagerness to 
play all the ends against the middle leads to his undoing in one of the darkest 
stories in the noir crime genre. 
</P>
</TEXT>
