<TEXT>
<P>
 FRANK LLOYD WRIGHT: West by Thomas A. Heinz (Gibbs-Smith: $12.95; 64 pp., 
illustrated, paperback original). Thomas Heinz's noteworthy survey of Wright's 
work continues with this volume devoted to buildings in Japan, Arizona and 
California, including the local landmarks, Ennis House and Hollyhock House. 
Heinz combines a brief, insightful text with well-chosen color photographs to 
present an educational overview of buildings as diverse as the bizarre, 
Mayan-influenced Ennis House in Los Feliz and the elegantly understated Marin 
County Library. 
</P>
