<P>
JUST CALL HIM TAFKAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As I was listening to some music at the house one evening last week, my 
roommate walked in and declared: "That sounds like Weird Androgynous Sign." 
</P>
<P>
 It took me a few moments to realize he was referring to that purple person 
from Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
 I've noticed that your staff has continuously struggled with how to refer to 
this pop musician since he decided he was to be known as . So I suggest that 
instead of "the pop star formerly known as . . . " or "we once knew him as . . 
. ," perhaps the easiest way to handle his logo-identification would be to call 
him Weird Androgynous Sign. 
</P>
<P>
 STRANGE CRYPTIC MARKING 
</P>
<P>
 (with ABSTRACT PERPENDICULAR DOODLE) 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
