<P>
BRIEFLY; BUSINESS: HOTEL GETS NEW MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Peter Kretschmann, former Capital Hilton manager in Washington, has replaced 
Richard Cotter as general manager of the Beverly Hilton Hotel in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Kretschmann, 41, began his career in 1970 in his native Germany. He worked 
throughout Europe and Israel before coming to the United States in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
 The huge hotel has 581 guest rooms, 24 meeting rooms and three ballrooms. 
