<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES CITY HALL JOURNAL: A SUMMARY OF SELECTED CITY HALL ACTIONS LAST 
WEEK THAT AFFECT THE WESTSIDE. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
<P>
 * COMMUNITY FUNDING -- Approved appropriating $3,600 in city money to 
partially fund 16 community organizations. Groups receiving funds include 
Venice Arts Mecca, West Los Angeles Booster Club, New Bethel Baptist Church in 
Venice, West Los Angeles Symphony and Westchester High School Academic Booster 
Club. 
</P>
<P>
 * RESTAURATEUR HONORED -- Approved a motion allowing the installation of a 
star on the sidewalk in front of Lucy's El Adobe restaurant at 5536 Melrose 
Ave. in honor of Frank Casado, who opened the eatery with his wife, Lucy, in 
1964. Casado died in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 * BLOCK PARTY -- Approved the street closure of Vicksburg Avenue, between 79th 
Street and 82nd Street, from noon to 6 p.m. on Monday for the Vicksburg Avenue 
Neighborhood Block Party. HOW THEY VOTED 
</P>
<P>
 * DOMESTIC VIOLENCE -- Directed the Los Angeles Housing Department to set 
aside $5 million annually for the development of new shelters for battered 
women, as well as the expansion of three existing shelters. Los Angeles Police 
Cmdr. John White said the goal was to have 18 shelters, one in each police 
division. Alana Bowman of the city attorney's office said the bed shortage at 
the existing shelters is so severe that two-thirds of the women who currently 
seek refuge are turned away for lack of room. She also said that only 3% of 
battered women end up reaching out to a shelter. Hotline number for assistance 
or advice on domestic violence issues is (310) 392-9896. Passed 14-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Voting yes: John Ferraro, Marvin Braude, Zev Yaroslavsky, Ruth Galanter, Mark 
Ridley-Thomas, Nate Holden, Jackie Goldberg. MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
