<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; TRY HERE FOR FRENCH FESTIVAL TICKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A company that has specialized in travel to France since 1987 is selling 
tickets for some of the major summer festivals and charging only a $20 
reservation fee, regardless of the number of tickets purchased.Major ticket 
agencies charge 15% to 20% per-ticket handling fees. 
</P>
<P>
 Henri Schaff, president of H.S.A. Voyages, says he has been building a network 
of sources at various festivals and has access to tickets for Choregies 
d'Orange, which runs from July 9-Aug. 2 (tickets range from $35 to $160), and 
Aix-en-Provence, July 15-30 (tickets $40-$170), among others. 
</P>
<P>
 Schaff can also get tickets for several French opera and ballet companies. For 
information, call (800) 927-4765. 
</P>
