<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; GETTING THE LATEST HURRICANE WORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's hurricane season and travelers bound for hurricane country -- the East 
and Gulf coasts and the Caribbean -- can call a 900 number to get the latest 
storm advisories from the forecasters at the National Hurricane Center in Coral 
Gables, Fla.Calls cost 98 cents a minute and the average call runs about three 
minutes. Reports are available 24 hours a day. Hurricane season runs from June 
1 to Nov. 31. The number is (900) 933-2628. 
</P>
