<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAGET POSTCARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 How wonderful to see the Pagets off once again ("Postcards From Paradise")! 
Two years ago, I turned to each week's installment of their trip across country 
first as I flipped through the Sunday Times. Now, what a treat to visit Hawaii 
through their eyes! 
</P>
<P>
 CINDY CHANG, Sherman Oaks 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Having vacationed in Hilo, Hawaii, (I find) the Pagets' travels bring back 
many happy memories, along with some unusual and interesting ones: Craving the 
delicious coffee bean candy and ending up with a good case of "java jitters" 
for two days was an interesting experience not to be repeated. Next time, we'll 
limit ourselves to one handful. And then there are the rains that keep 
everything clean and bright and explain the burst of blossoms everywhere, 
permeating the air with warm sweet fragrances. I'm grateful to the Pagets for 
helping me recall these memories. 
</P>
<P>
 PAULA LORAINE McINTOSH, Lake Forest 
