<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXPLORING THEORY OF STRESS, CANCER LINK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I would like to offer my theory to Dr. Hoda Anton-Culver why Orange County 
women have a breast cancer rate twice that of the nation.("Hunt Goes On for 
Clues to Higher Rate of Breast Cancer Locally," commentary on health, June 26). 
There is a theory Dr. Anton-Culver didn't talk about, that breast cancer is 
caused by elevated stress levels. 
</P>
<P>
 I have traveled extensively and I have said for years that Orange County women 
are the most "stressed out" women in the nation. By "stressed out," I mean high 
worry levels about material things and status. I think it is a theory worth 
investigating. 
</P>
<P>
 GREG HILL 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
