<HEADLINE>
<P>
IMPLICATIONS OF U.S. LABOR STUDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Well, the Clinton health plan for America is already at work! With 
prescription in hand, Labor Secretary Robert Reich ordered up a study of U.S. 
workers that was clearly designed to discover an illness to support the Clinton 
Administration's diagnosis of what's wrong with America ("Federal Study Paints 
a Grim Picture of the Workplace," June 3). 
</P>
<P>
 The Administration's overriding goal, of course -- as with everything they 
prescribe for American business -- is the expansion of government and the 
political class as America's new royalty.They do this by creating studies that 
show this country as unfair, as an engine of poverty, as racist -- or that 
demonstrate ever-widening gaps between rich and poor. 
</P>
<P>
 Defining the problem as between haves and have-nots as Reich does reveals the 
real agenda. The solution is always the same: We need ever-growing government 
and the elites in charge to redistribute income from the so-called rich to the 
poor in America (first raking off their share for these wonderful activities). 
</P>
<P>
 KIP DELLINGER 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
