<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST: HOME IMPROVEMENT / GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Check brown spots in lawns for sodweb worms and grubs. 
</P>
<P>
 * If the foliage is dry and yellowed on spring blooming bulbs, be sure to cut 
if off. Divide and replant any crowded clumps of bulbs for better bloom next 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant garden mums now for a blaze of color this fall. 
</P>
<P>
 * Feed tuberous begonias and fuchsias with 0-10-10 fertilizer. 
</P>
<P>
 * Divide and transplant bearded iris. 
</P>
