<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: USC AREA; AREA REVITALIZATION PLAN TO BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Redevelopment Agency is sponsoring a community meeting to 
discuss a preliminary draft plan of a five-year project for redevelopment of 
the USC area July 14. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6:30 p.m. meeting at the Los Angeles Child Guidance Clinic, 3787 S. 
Vermont Ave., will focus on plans to revitalize the area bounded by Vermont and 
Wisconsin avenues on the west, the Harbor Freeway on the east, Adams Boulevard 
on the north and 41st Street on the south. Residents, merchants and community 
organizers are encouraged to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 766-9825. 
</P>
