<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: USC; LISTINGS SOUGHT FOR LATINO DIRECTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC is accepting listings for its bilingual resource directory from area 
nonprofit organizations that service the Latino community. 
</P>
<P>
 The Directory of the Hispanic Community of the County of Los Angeles lists 
more than 1,000 cultural, civic, social, sports, political, business, media and 
service organizations. The publication is a guide for individuals and groups 
wishing to reach the Latino community. 
</P>
<P>
 The listings are published at no cost as part of the university's community 
outreach project. To be included in the directory, organizations must fill out 
a request form provided by USC. The deadline for submission is Aug. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 740-5480. 
</P>
