<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WILSHIRE / KOREATOWN; PUBLIC URGED TO HELP PLAN 
REDEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Wilshire Center and Koreatown Community Advisory Committee invites 
residents, merchants and property owners to attend its regular monthly meeting 
Thursday at Southwestern University School of Law, 675 S. Westmoreland Ave. The 
meeting begins at 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee, which advises the City Council and the Community Redevelopment 
Agency, is drafting a redevelopment plan for the two communities and encourages 
discussion on issues related to the revitalization of the area, including 
public safety and housing. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 977-2633. 
