COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 8 ARRESTED ON SUSPICION OF DRUNK DRIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Highway Patrol arrested eight people in Ventura County on 
suspicion of drunk driving during the first 12 hours of the Fourth of July 
weekend, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorists were arrested between 6 p.m. Friday and 6 a.m. Saturday, a CHP 
spokeswoman said. Although there were several injury accidents during the same 
period, none were attributed to drunk driving, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP's maximum enforcement period will end at 6 p.m. Monday, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 A final tally of arrests from the long holiday weekend will be released 
Tuesday.SCOTT HADLY 
