<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUNIOR COLLEGE CAMP LURES TOP PLAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Markee Brown will be one of five Los Angeles City College basketball players 
competing in the 5th annual West Coast Junior College Camp at UC Riverside, 
July 15-17. 
</P>
<P>
 Games start at 2:45 p.m. on July 15, 9:30 a.m. on July 16 and 11 a.m. on July 
17. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-day event features 46 players from 28 teams.  
</P>
<P>
 Players include 6-2 Davy Fortson of Santa Monica, former Dorsey High star, 6-5 
Rashaan Johnson of Ventura and 6-4 Larry Reed of Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, a 6-2 sophomore, led the Cubs in scoring last year at 18 points a game 
and is considered one of the top community college prospects for next season. 
</P>
<P>
 Joining Brown will be sophomores Sai Tuialli, formerly of South Gate, and 
Derrick Brown; and freshmen Charles Adams and Calvin Patterson, formerly a 
Fremont guard. 
</P>
<P>
 Patterson, a 6-2 guard who, like Brown, is a premier three-point shooter, was 
a 1994 City Times All-Star First Team selection. 
</P>
<P>
 LACC will also be competing in the Ballstars Junior College All-American Camp 
July 9-11 at Vincennes University in Indiana and July 29-31 at the University 
of West Florida in Pensacola. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ballstars Camp is open to 1995 sophomores-to-be, unsigned 1994 sophomores 
still seeking a school and incoming junior college freshmen who want to 
compete. 
</P>
<P>
 The camp fee is $170. 
</P>
<P>
 Players from colleges in California, New York, Texas, Florida and Michigan 
will compete. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Rick Ball (314) 921-8647. 
</P>
