<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 ROUND OF 16; SPOTLIGHT; HE'LL BE READY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lothar Matthaeus, captain of the German team, was replaced at halftime because 
of the foot injury he suffered in his team's final first-round match against 
South Korea. 
</P>
<P>
 Matthaeus, who plays sweeper, was spiked on his left foot. The injury required 
six stitches. He took an injection of a pain-killer before Saturday's game but 
was in obvious pain during the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Matthaeus said he expects to play all of his team's quarterfinal game. CHRIS 
DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070394-0281 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 057308 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
