</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The biggest problem for Belgium was helping its fans get to Chicago for its 
game Saturday against Germany. 
</P>
<P>
 About 10,000 Belgian fans were in South Florida, expecting to stay for a 
Belgium-Ireland match Tuesday. However, Belgium's 1-0 loss to Saudi Arabia on 
Wednesday sent the Belgians to Chicago instead. Scheduled flights out of 
Orlando simply couldn't accommodate the hordes of followers. 
</P>
<P>
 "If 500 fans from Belgium are in Chicago, that would be a success," said Roger 
van den Stock, an official of the Belgian Football Assn. before the game. 
</P>
<P>
 After a 3-2 loss to Germany, the Belgians can go home. HELENE ELLIOTT 
