<P>
 Swiss fans Kelly Kubisiak and Darrly Chesley from Virginia won smiles wherever 
they went at RFK Stadium on Saturday.Kubisiak was the one wearing the 
4-foot-long hat that looked like a large piece of well-known yellow cheese. 
Chesley's had the red knife with its trademark gray cross. 
</P>
<P>
 "We thought of hats with chocolate, a cow and a dollar bill. And we actually 
tried one that looked like a watch -- but it was slow," Chesley said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither man has spent time in Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Swiss happen to be playing in the only game we could get tickets for," 
said Kubisiak, the hat maker. Construction time: "about one case of beer." 
WILLIAM D. MONTALBANO 
