<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 ROUND OF 16; SPOTLIGHT; IS THERE FIRE HYDRANT IN THE END 
ZONE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL PLASCHKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two weeks remain in the World Cup, but the award for the strangest post-goal 
celebration has been clinched by Nigeria's Finidi George. 
</P>
<P>
 After scoring the first goal in Nigeria's final first-round victory over 
Greece, George ran into the corner of the end zone, fell to the ground on all 
fours and began barking. 
</P>
<P>
 After his teammates surrounded him, he lifted his right leg. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was just a dance of happiness. We do those dances all the time," teammate 
Sunday Oliseh said. "The dance that Finidi did, in Nigeria, we do that at 
parties." BILL PLASCHKE 
