<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAUGUS SPEEDWAY; MINTEY ANGRY AFTER LOSING TO WOODSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tempers flared following the Sportsman main event Saturday night at Saugus 
Speedway and as a result defending track champion Pat Mintey Jr. of Quartz Hill 
has vowed not to return to the one-third of a mile oval. 
</P>
<P>
 Things heated up following the 30-lap feature race won by Sean Woodside of 
Saugus over a controversial pass on the 14th lap. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm not coming back," said Mintey, who led Woodside by 15 points before the 
race. "We'll find somewhere else to race." 
</P>
<P>
 Mintey lost the lead to Woodside after the two made contact coming out of turn 
two. Mintey finished seventh and was upset that Woodside was not penalized. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodside had a different view. 
</P>
<P>
 "I got underneath him once before . . . that's what this is from," Woodside 
said, pointing to a black mark on the front spoiler of his car. "I got under 
him again and he tried to cut down on me and he lost it." 
</P>
<P>
 Woodside held off a strong challenge from former champion Gary Sigman of 
Carson to register his second victory and eighth top five finish in 10 starts 
this season. 
</P>
