<TEXT>
<P>
 Goalie Rob Laurie made 64 saves to lead the Bullfrogs to a 9-6 victory over 
the San Diego Barracudas in a Roller Hockey International game Saturday night 
at the San Diego Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs, who lost to the Barracudas a week ago, quickly posted a 3-0 
lead midway through the second quarter on two goals by Victor Gervais and one 
by Darren Perkins. 
</P>
<P>
 The Barracudas battled back with goals by Marc Savard and Danny Gravelle in a 
65-second span. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs made it 4-2 at halftime on Jim Brown's power-play goal. 
</P>
<P>
