took its first lead when Darcy Norton scored at 1 minute 15 seconds of the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Bullfrogs scored the final four goals, including Brown's game-winner 
on a power play at 4:44 of the final quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs improve to 8-1-0; San Diego dropped to 6-4-1. 
</P>
