<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; WASHINGTON, D.C.; RENO SAID TO SEEK COUNSEL IN ESPY CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Atty. Gen. Janet Reno is ready to ask for the appointment of an independent 
counsel to take over the inquiry into Agriculture Secretary Mike Espy's links 
to an Arkansas-based poultry producer, a newspaper reported.But a Justice 
Department official called the New York Times report "a matter of speculation 
at this point." The Justice Department has been looking into whether Espy 
violated the 1907 Meat Inspection Act by accepting football tickets and an 
airplane trip from Tyson Foods. Espy said he expects to be cleared because he 
reimbursed Tyson for all costs. 
</P>
